
[1]halberd

   HAL'BERD, n. A military weapon, consisting of a pole or shaft of wood,
   with a head armed with a steel point, with a cross piece of steel, flat
   and pointed at both ends, or with a cutting edge at one end, and a bent
   point at the other. It is carried by sergeants of foot and dragoons.
